title: Arizona Libertarian Party
deleted: The Libertarian party's most successful candidate in 2014 by both percentage and votes was Maricopa County Assessor candidate Rebecca Kielsky with 208,394, or 29.26% of the votes.

title: Arizona Libertarian Party
added: During the [[2008 United States presidential election|2008 presidential election]] the Libertarian Party declined a government-financed presidential primary and instead held its own private primary online. Less than seventy voters participated in the private primary that was won by George Phillies.<ref>{{Cite news |date=December 4, 2007 |title=Arizona Libertarian Party Declines Having Presidential Primary |work=[[Ballot Access News]] |url=http://ballot-access.org/2007/12/04/arizona-libertarian-party-declines-having-presidential-primary/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.vn/yOdxX |archive-date=September 22, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=March 6, 2008 |title=Arizona Libertarian Private Presidential Primary |work=[[Ballot Access News]] |url=http://ballot-access.org/2008/03/06/arizona-libertarian-private-presidential-primary/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.vn/mqLdg |archive-date=September 22, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=February 6, 2008 |title=Libertarian Presidential Primaries |work=[[Ballot Access News]] |url=http://ballot-access.org/2008/02/06/libertarian-presidential-primaries/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.vn/crlYj |archive-date=September 22, 2020}}</ref>
